{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"19a402df-37e3-44f9-bb07-8a88fc7b2178","content":"This TUnit project uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)**, so you need `--treenode-filter` (not `--filter`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThe treenode path format is `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Method`, so `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` matches any assembly, any namespace, the `SmsNotificationTests` class, and all its methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"39bc3919-f496-423a-9b39-460646035f12","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) by default. For MTP-based test runners, filtering by class uses the `--treenode-filter` option with the appropriate syntax.\n\nFor TUnit on MTP, the filter to run only `SmsNotificationTests` would be:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nWait, let me think about TUnit's filter syntax. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. The treenode filter syntax for MTP is `--treenode-filter` with a path-like pattern.\n\n\nThe treenode filter format follows an assembly/namespace/class/method structure, so to match all tests in the `SmsNotificationTests` class, I'd use a wildcard pattern at the end to capture all methods within that class.","outputTokens":523,"requestId":"7C18:1E67:172AEC:1BDDFE:69F94841"},"id":"d7c186ec-02eb-48a8-8480-82485b111420","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:30:53.612Z","parentId":"b9cb5ec9-0721-4988-970b-8b3e1e557516"}
